    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.judgePrompt }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a strict evaluator of study plans. You are given the INPUTS (study goal, self-assessed level, handbook text, learning preferences), the STUDENT RATING the human gave (1-5), a STUDENT COMMENT ANALYSIS, and the PLAN.\n\nUse the student's rating and comment as real human signal: where the student raised a concern, weigh it; where they praised something, take that into account. Do NOT change the student's rating — it is recorded separately. Score the PLAN on four criteria, each 1-5 (5 = excellent):\n- grounding: uses only deadlines/weights actually present in the handbook; says when a deadline is unknown; invents nothing.\n- calibration: difficulty, pacing and assumed prior knowledge match the self-assessed level.\n- actionability: sessions are concrete (topic + duration + intended output); the weekly schedule is realistic.\n- honesty: states trade-offs when time is tight; does not over-promise.\n\nReturn ONLY a JSON object, no prose, no code fences:\n{\"grounding\":N,\"calibration\":N,\"actionability\":N,\"honesty\":N,\"overall\":N,\"notes\":\"one sentence\"}"
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        1248,
        0
      ],
      "id": "038c4bda-5bc8-458d-9faf-5c184958bc7c",
      "name": "Judge Agent"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "model": "gemma4:26b-a4b-it-qat",
        "options": {
          "numPredict": -1,
          "format": "json"
        }
      },
